The paper discusses regularization techniques in linear system identification, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization problems and numerical analysis, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of regularization techniques in system identification is also relevant to cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.SY (Control Theory and Systems).
